  • Interface Summary 
    Interface Description
    SearchTree<E>
    5 down vote accepted In contrast to AVL trees where rotations for deletions may propagate up to the root (although having at most one (double-)rotation for insert), RB trees require a constant (at most 2 for insert, at most 3 for deletion) number of rotations.
